<%# THEMED flag for specialized puzzles — so people can dodge them or chase
    them. The chip alone ("Themed") doesn't tell you *what* the theme is, so the
    tags always ride alongside it inline (`inline_tags`): the browse card + show
    page both name the theme up front. A span wrapper (not <p>) so it can nest
    inside the card's whole-row anchor. Classic puzzles render nothing.
    Expects `puzzle`. %>
<% if puzzle.specialized? %>
  <span class="m-themed m-themed--inline">
    <span class="m-themed__chip">Themed</span>
    <% puzzle.tags.each do |tag| %>
      <span class="m-themed__tag"><%= tag.name %></span>
    <% end %>
  </span>
<% end %>
